    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Automated Post-Purchase Google Review Request With Support Check",
        "height": 112,
        "width": 1208,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "cfb5dc25-4e21-4a97-a749-6a2a95a00b81",
      "name": "Note: Automated Post-Purchase Google Review Request With Support Check",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1968,
        -256
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Overview\nWhen order.updated fires, this workflow sends a delayed Google review request only if the order is completed and no complaint is open:\n\n1. Filter for status equals completed\n2. Look up the customer in Gorgias by billing email\n3. Check for any open tickets\n4. Skip sending if a complaint exists\n5. Get product category from WooCommerce\n6. Set dynamic wait days by category\n7. Generate email body with AI\n8. Build review link and email data\n9. Wait the calculated days\n10. Send Gmail review request\n11. Log pending review to Google Sheets",
        "height": 408,
        "width": 476,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "cc46a6ac-a5d5-4ae9-b1d4-ae18b79f7c1c",
      "name": "Note: Overview1",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2832,
        -32
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Node-by-node Purpose\n\n1. Order Completed Trigger\nEvent order.updated — Listens for WooCommerce order updates via webhook\n\n2. Is Order Completed?\nIF status equals completed — Continue to Gorgias if true, else go to Ignore\n\n3. Ignore - Not Completed\nType noOp — Ends workflow for orders not completed\n\n4. Gorgias Get Customer\nQueries Gorgias for customer using billing email\n\n5. Extract Gorgias Customer ID\nCode extracts first customer ID from response or null\n\n6. Gorgias List Open Tickets\nLists open tickets for that customer\n\n7. Check Has Complaint\nCode sets hasComplaint true if any tickets exist\n\n8. Has Open Complaint?\nIF hasComplaint true — Stop workflow if true, else continue\n\n9. Stop - Support Handling First\nType noOp — Ends to prioritize support\n\n10. Get Product Category\nFetches WooCommerce product data for first line item\n\n11. Determine Delay and Category\nCode sets delay 2 days for beauty food consumable, 10 days for electronics, 5 days default\n\n12. AI Generate Review Email\nModel gpt-4o-mini — Generates warm plain text email\n\n13. Build Review Link and Email Data\nPrepares review link, email body, and customer data\n\n14. Wait Before Sending Dynamic Delay\nWaits the calculated days based on category\n\n15. Send Review Request Email\nSends Gmail to customer with subject and review link\n\n16. Log Pending Review\nAppends order data to Google Sheets sheet PendingReviews",
        "height": 756,
        "width": 680,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "4de9af8d-1dec-4c9d-b2a7-7a32b5434f94",
      "name": "Note: Node-by-node Purpose",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1200,
        -192
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Auto-Reward Google Reviewers With Coupons",
        "height": 80,
        "width": 824,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "baacaf08-b2ea-47d8-88f0-7e1ac5411399",
      "name": "Note: Title",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1776,
        912
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Overview\nWhen the schedule fires every 6 hours, this workflow polls Google reviews and rewards matched customers with coupons:\n\n1. Fetch Google Business reviews via API\n2. Load pending customers from Google Sheets\n3. Fuzzy-match reviewers to customers by name\n4. Create a WooCommerce coupon and email it\n5. Mark the customer as fulfilled in the sheet",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 396,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "00156307-833d-4388-9e90-c5177ed2cd86",
      "name": "Note: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2704,
        960
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Node-by-node Purpose\n\n1. Poll Google Reviews (Every 6h)\nTriggers automatically every 6 hours.\n\n2. Set Google Business Config\nStores the account ID and location ID for the API call.\n\n3. Fetch Google Business Reviews\nCalls Google My Business API to get all reviews.\n\n4. Get Pending Reviews\nReads rows from the PendingReviews sheet where reviewed is false.\n\n5. Fuzzy Match Reviewer To Customer\nCompares reviewer names to customer names using fuzzy logic and checks if the review was posted after the email date.\n\n6. Match Found?\nIf the similarity score is 0.6 or higher, proceed to reward. If not, skip this cycle.\n\n7. No Match This Cycle\nEnds the path when no match is found.\n\n8. Create Thank You Coupon\nCreates a new WooCommerce coupon code.\n\n9. Send Thank You Email With Coupon\nEmails the customer a personalized thank-you message with their coupon code.\n\n10. Mark Review Fulfilled\nUpdates the sheet to set reviewed to true and saves the coupon code.",
        "height": 596,
        "width": 472,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "e2dfff1f-0a58-43ec-9af7-e148e3ffcd2c",
      "name": "Note: Node-by-node",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        48,
        864
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=={{ \n'Customer name: ' + $json.customerName + \n'. Items ordered: ' + $json.lineItems + \n'. Category type: ' + $json.categoryType + \n'. Days since delivery: ' + $json.delayDays + \n'. Write only the email body asking for a Google review. Mention the products by name, make it feel personal to the category, and keep it under 110 words. Do not include any link, signature, or subject.'\n}}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
